efined introduction  personal information bb and its affiliated companies we us respect your online privacy and recognize your need for appropriate protection and management of your personally identifiable information personal information that we may acquire in your use of our site we may collect personal information from you if we do you will be expressly asked for it so that you know what information you are providing we also collect nonpersonal information described below nonpersonal information we may use reporting technologies on our site to record nonpersonal information such as internet domain and host names internet protocol ip addresses the page you request your browser software and operating system types clickstream patterns and dates and times that our site is accessed we analyze this information for trends and statistics our use of tracking technologies allows us to improve our site helps us understand the demographics of our user base and suggests the sorts of announcements you are likely to have an interest in our site may utilize cookies a cookie is a small text file placed on your computers hard drive that allows our site to recognize you as a prior user determine which pages you have previously seen and so on we also may use cookies to deliver content to you that you might be particularly interested in we cannot determine your identity from our use of cookies we may store the information collected through cookies in our databases you may be able to configure your browser to notify you if you receive a cookie to block cookies or to remove cookies from your computer however if you do so it may be more difficult for you to navigate our site these technologies are not designed to identify you it may be possible to identify you and your online actions through the use of cookies and ip addresses but only in conjunction with personal information you have voluntarily provided to us protection of personal information we restrict access to the personal information we have collected from or about you as described above to those employees who need to know the information to provide services to you we maintain physical electronic and procedural safeguards to guard your personal information despite our use of commercially reasonable efforts to protect your personal information from unauthorized access or disclosure the internet is not an inherently secure environment and so we cannot guarantee the security of your personal information we assume no liability for any disclosure of data due to errors in transmission unauthorized third party access or other acts of third parties or acts or omissions beyond our reasonable control use of personal information we may collect personal information when you sign up to receive newsletters that we may publish from time to time request information regarding an event we may sponsor and otherwise as needed to fulfill your requests for information and services and to contact you when we collect this information you will know it because you will need to submit this information to us in order to receive the information or service you requested we use personal information primarily for our own internal purposes such as evaluating what aspects of the site need improvement fulfilling your requests for information or services and communicating with you we also use personal information for our direct marketing purposes and we will use the information to send you announcements and invitations in which we think you may have interest you can always opt out of these marketing uses by telling us not to send the materials to you when you provide the personal information or by asking us to remove you from those mailing lists this is normally done by clicking on the appropriate link in those mailings you can also contact us at infobrudermanbrotherscom we cannot delete all the personal information that you provide to us even if you ask us to do so if you choose not to provide us with the personal information that we request you can still visit most of our site but you may be unable to obtain certain information or services that we offer disclosure of personal information in the ordinary course of our business we do not rent or sell any personal information we collect from or about you for the purposes specified above we may transfer or disclose any personal information we have collected from or about you to any of our affiliated entities we may disclose your personal information as permitted by law and may also be required to disclose your personal information to governmental or regulatory entities in response to regulatory inquiries in connection with investigations or to comply with applicable law rules regulations orders subpoenas or other legal processes we may disclose all of the information we collect from or about you including personal information as described above to companies that perform marketing services on our behalf or to other financial institutions with whom we have joint marketing agreements these thirdparty service providers help us maintain our site and deliver information and services to you and other users of our site and help us analyze our site traffic the companies we hire to provide such support services are not allowed to use your personal information for their own purposes and are contractually obligated to protect your personal information we do not transfer personal information to third parties for their use as a mailing list or for other advertising purposes as an exception your personal information may be used by any company with which we merge acquire or are acquired by we may also use it in the event of bankruptcy in the event our privacy policy is modified due to such merger acquisition bankruptcy or for any other reason notice of the revised privacy policy will be posted on this site access accuracy and deletion of data upon your written request we will allow you to review any of your personal information that you disclosed to us 